- A cache is a small, fast memory location that stores frequently accessed data or instructions; 
- L2 cache is a type of cache memory that is larger and slower than L1 cache but faster and smaller than the main memory;
- Average bandwidth measures the average rate of data transfer over a communication link, expressed in GB/s (gigabytes per second).

